        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 28 at 3:17PM EDT until June 28 at 3:45PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 317 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Shippingport,
or 7 miles east of East Liverpool, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
East Liverpool, Wellsville, Beaver, Calcutta, Ohioville, Midland,
Chester, Industry, Shippingport, Newell, Georgetown, Hookstown,
Glasgow, La Croft, Tomlinson Run State Park and Glenmoor.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds.</instruction>
